''We try to assist people in writing letters to their representatives and to collect responses that have been coming in, to learn from this, so as to enable true communication between citizens and their representatives that is beneficial to both sides.''

== News & Chronology ==

 * 2005-04-07 phm proposes [:MepsQuest05En: 5-step Questionnaire/Checklist for Software Patent Legislators]
 * 2005-03-28 [:LtrFfiiMeps050329En: FFII distributes a letter with appendices on paper to all MEPs] pointing to a [:Plen05En: page with ressources for MEPs]
 * 2005-03-29 EU [:Plen05En: FFII distributes letter with position paper to all MEPs]
 * 2005-03-24 CH [http://euparl.patentpolitics.info/ Patentpolitics.info: Norbert Bollow launches letter-writing initiative] (phm: good organisation effort, some letters texts less good)
 * 2005-03-15 EU [:LtrFfiiCons050308En: FFII: FFII sends 23 procedural questions to the Council Legal Services] (-> [:Cons050307En: Adoption Farce])
 * 2005-03-10 EU [:LtrFfiiCons050308En: FFII: Letter to the Council Presidency: What happened on Monday?] (-> [:Cons050307En: Adoption Farce])
 * 2005-03-06 DE [:LtrCons0503En: FFII launches Thank Denmark Campaign to Support B-Item Move]
